Tufyal Choudhury is a lecturer in international human rights law at Durham University, England.[1] His research interests focus on equality law and in particular on racial and religious discrimination. He is a director of the Discrimination Law Association,[2] an adviser to the Discrimination Law Project for Justice,[3] and to the human rights organisation JUSTICE,[3] and consultant on a variety of associated projects. His research into conditions for Muslims in the United Kingdom has been cited at a national level.[1][4] He is a joint author of Democracy under Blair: A Democratic Audit of the United Kingdom.[5] 
